{"title_page": "Sonequa Martin-Green", "text_new": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\t\n| name        = Sonequa Martin-Green\t\n| image       = File:Sonequa Martin-Green 2019 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size  = 250px\n| caption     = Martin-Green at the 2019 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\t\n| birth_name  = Sonequa Martin\t\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1985|03|21}}\t\n| birth_place = [[Russellville, Alabama]], U.S.\n| alma_mater  = [[University of Alabama]]\n| occupation  = Actress, producer\n| years_active = 2005\u2013present\t\n| residence   = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S.\t\n| spouse      = {{marriage|[[Kenric Green]]|2010}}\t\n| children = 1\n}}\n\n'''Sonequa Martin-Green''' ({{IPAc-en|s|\u0259|\u02c8|n|i\u02d0|k|w|\u0259}};<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rYr-ttyZ_PQ|title=Sonequa Martin-Green {{!}} Behind the Scenes GH|work=Good Housekeeping|date=October 14, 2015|accessdate=March 28, 2019}}</ref> born March 21, 1985)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/WalkingDead_AMC/status/844247347932663808|title=We're all in for @SonequaMG's birthday. #TWD|last=@WalkingDead_AMC|date=2017-03-21|website=Twitter|accessdate=2017-04-04}}</ref> is an American actress and producer. She is best known for her television roles as [[Michael Burnham]], the main character in the [[web television]] series ''[[Star Trek: Discovery]]'', and as [[Sasha Williams (The Walking Dead)|Sasha Williams]] on ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.highlighthollywood.com/2012/12/31/actress-sonequa-martin-green-does-double-duty-on-abcs-once-upon-a-time-and-amcs-the-walking-dead-highlight-hollywood-news/|title=Actress Sonequa Martin-Green Does Double Duty On ABC's 'Once Upon A Time' And AMC's 'The Walking Dead', Highlight Hollywood News|last=Garrett|first=Tommy Lightfoot|date=2012-12-31|website=Highlight Hollywood|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref> Before that, she had starred in several [[independent films]] before gaining her first recurring role as Courtney Wells on ''[[The Good Wife]]''. Later, she had recurring roles as Tamara in ''[[Once Upon a Time (TV series)|Once Upon a Time]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/12/31/once-upon-time-spoilers-cast-sonequa-martin-green-as-tamara/|title='Once Upon a Time' Season 2 Spoilers \u2014 Sonequa Martin-Green as Tamara|last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|date=2012-12-31|website=TVLine|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/12/31/sonequa-martin-green-once-upon-a-time_n_2389782.html |title='Walking Dead' Actress Sonequa Martin-Green Is Headed To 'Once Upon A Time'|date=2012-12-31|work=HuffPost|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref name=\"Published Wednesday, Jan 2 2013, 18:08 GMT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ustv/s181/once-upon-a-time/news/a438508/walking-dead-actress-sonequa-martin-green-joins-once-upon-a-time.html|title='Walking Dead' actress Sonequa Martin-Green joins 'Once Upon a Time'|last=Fletcher|first=Alex|date=2013-01-02|website=Digital Spy|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.al.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2013/01/ua_theatre_alum_sonequea_marti.html|title=UA theatre alum Sonequa Martin-Green lands role on ABC hit 'Once Upon a Time'|last=Flanagan|first=Ben|date=2013-01-03|website=Al.com|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref> and Rhonda in ''[[New Girl]]''. \n\n==Early life==\nMartin-Green was born in [[Russellville, Alabama]]. She has one sister and three older half-sisters. She had initially planned to become a [[psychologist]] before deciding to pursue a career in acting when she was in the tenth grade.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wetpaint.com/sonequa-martin-green-5-things-611007/|title=Sonequa Martin-Green: 5 Things You Didn't Know About The Walking Dead Star|last=Lloyd|first=Sarah|date=2013-10-23|work=Wetpaint|access-date=2017-09-07|language=en-US}}</ref> On her decision to become an actor, she said, \"I didn't know I was going to be an actor until I was 16. I thought I was going to be a psychologist, which is interesting because it's very similar to acting. I was fascinated with human behavior and why people do what they do. I was in the middle of rehearsal in 10th grade when I had this epiphany. And so I got my theatre degree from the University of Alabama.\"<ref>{{Cite news|title=Sonequa Martin-Green Shines Bright On Star Trek: Discovery|url=http://www.star2.com/entertainment/2017/09/28/sonequa-martin-green-trek-discovery/|last=Berk|first=Philip|date=2017-09-28|work=star2|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAfter graduating from the [[University of Alabama]] in 2007 with a degree in theatre,<ref name=\"UAalum\">{{cite web|url=http://www.al.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2013/04/ua_alum_sonequa_martin-green_u.html|title=UA alum Sonequa Martin-Green upgraded to 'The Walking Dead' series regular|last=Flanagan|first=Ben|date=April 4, 2013|work=AL.com|accessdate=April 5, 2013}}</ref> she relocated to [[New York City]] where she and her husband, Kenric, lived for five years before moving to [[California]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Film===\nWhile known primarily for her television roles, Sonequa Martin-Green made her film debut in 2009. In 2009, she played the lead role of Tosha Spinner in ''Toe to Toe'' opposite [[Louisa Krause]], the fiercely determined scholarship student who seeks to build a brighter future outside of [[Anacostia]] and away from one of [[Washington, D.C.|Washington]]'s poorest neighborhoods. The film focuses on her friendship and rivalry with Jessie (Louisa Krause), a privileged girl from [[Bethesda, Maryland|Bethesda]] whose promiscuous tendencies threaten to become her undoing. They both strive to gain a better understanding of one another's plight as society threatens to drive them ever farther apart. The film received generally positive reviews, with Martin-Green's performance receiving critical acclaim,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hollywoodandfine.com/%E2%80%98toe-to-toe%E2%80%99-face-to-face-with-race/|title='Toe to Toe': Face to face with race|last=Fine|first=Marchall|date=2010-02-25|website=Hollywood & Fine|language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/04/01/AR2010040100887.html | work=The Washington Post | first=Ann | last=Hornaday | title=Movie review: 'Toe to Toe,' a teen lacrosse drama Washingtonians will recognize | date=2010-04-02}}</ref> even from the film's detractors.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://nypost.com/2010/02/26/schoolgirls-stuck-in-stereotype/ | work=New York Post | first=V.A. | last=Musetto | title=Schoolgirls stuck in stereotype | date=2010-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/toe_to_toe/|title=Toe to Toe|website=Rotten Tomatoes|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref> In November 2018, it was announced Martin-Green would star in ''[[The Outside Story]]'', opposite [[Brian Tyree Henry]], directed by Casimir Nozkowski.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/sonequa-martin-green-brian-tyree-henry-the-outside-story-movie-1202510281/|title=Sonequa Martin-Green Joins Brian Tyree Henry In \u2018The Outside Story\u2019 Movie|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=November 28, 2018|accessdate=November 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Television===\n[[File:Sonequa Martin-Green 2016.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Sonequa Martin-Green at the 2016 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]] for ''The Walking Dead''.]]\nMartin-Green has had various guest and recurring roles in TV shows. She made her television debut in 2008, appearing on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'' as Kiana Richmond. She then gained her first recurring role on ''[[Army Wives]]'' as Kanessa Jones the following year. In 2009, she received the role of Courtney Wells on ''[[The Good Wife]]'', her first recurring role playing an adult character as opposed to playing a teenager with her previous roles in both film and television. She appeared on the show for two years before making two more appearances in ''[[Gossip Girl]]'' and ''[[NYC 22]]'' in 2011.\n\nIn 2012, she was cast in a recurring role on ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]'' as [[Sasha Williams (The Walking Dead)|Sasha]], the sister of Tyreese ([[Chad Coleman]]), an original character, exclusive to the television series.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/walking-dead-season-3-finale-interview-robert-kirkman-431968 |title='Walking Dead' Dissection: Robert Kirkman on the Major Fatalities and Comic Book Detour |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=2013-01-04 |accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref> Martin-Green auditioned for the role of [[Michonne]] albeit with a pseudonym due to the secrecy of the auditioning process. When [[Danai Gurira]], who Martin-Green said was \"the perfect choice\", was cast, former showrunner [[Glen Mazzara]] still wanted Martin-Green to be a part of the show and decided to create a role specifically for her instead. Martin-Green explained: \"[Sasha] was supposed to be a recurring character and as we kept going forward, they picked up my option to be a regular. It's very rare and I'm still quite dumbfounded about it but Glen and I hit it off and I still appreciate him. He wanted to work with me and wrote Sasha for me.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/gallery/walking-dead-audition-stories-815523/18-sonequa-martingreen-sasha |title='The Walking Dead' Audition Tales: 26 Stars Tell All |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=2015-08-20 |accessdate=2015-08-22}}</ref> She was promoted to a series regular for season 4 with [[Emily Kinney]] and Coleman.<ref>{{cite web|last=Slezak |first=Michael |url=http://tvline.com/2013/04/03/the-walking-dead-season-4-cast-tyreese-sasha-beth-series-regulars/ |title=The Walking Dead's Season 4 Cast \u2014 Tyreese, Sasha, Beth Upgraded To Series Regulars |publisher=TVLine |date= |accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Abrams |first=Natalie |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/entertainment/tv/tvguide/article/The-Walking-Dead-Promotes-Chad-Coleman-Sonequa-4407815.php |title=The Walking Dead Promotes Chad Coleman, Sonequa Martin-Green and More to Series Regular |publisher=seattlepi.com |date= |accessdate=2013-04-04 }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/walking-dead-season-4-spoilers-tyreese-beth-sasha-432869 |title='Walking Dead' Promotes Three to Series Regular for Season 4 |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=2013-03-04 |accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/603070/the-walking-dead-promotes-three-to-series-regulars/ |title='The Walking Dead' Promotes Three To Series Regulars |publisher=Inquisitr.com |date=2009-11-15 |accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref>\n\nAfter auditioning for the role of Michonne, she read the first three volumes of the graphic novels in preparation for the television series. Knowing they were different, she chose not to continue reading the comic book series to avoid being aware of future storylines that may occur on the television series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3WR6Pt29_Dc|title=Sonequa Martin-Green (AMC's Walking Dead) Interview - AfterBuzz TV's Spotlight On|first=|last=AfterBuzz TV|date=17 February 2014|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> Martin-Green's performance as Sasha, particularly in the [[The Walking Dead (season 5)|fifth season]]<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/the-walking-dead-try-review-ricks-vendetta-against-paul-intensifies-as-finale-looms-10129148.html | location=London | work=The Independent | first=Alex | last=Straker | title=The Walking Dead, Try \u2013 review: Rick Grimes' vendetta against Paul intensifies as finale looms | date=2015-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/tv/the-walking-dead/34129/the-walking-dead-season-5-episode-10-review-them|title=The Walking Dead season 5 episode 10 review: Them|last=Hogan|first=Ron|date=2015-02-16|work=Den of Geek|access-date=2017-09-07|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/tv/the-walking-dead/34461/the-walking-dead-season-5-episode-13-review-forget|title=The Walking Dead season 5 episode 13 review: Forget|last=Hogan|first=Ron|date=2015-03-10|website=Den of Geek|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref> and  [[The Walking Dead (season 7)|seventh season]], has received favorable reviews.<ref name=paste>{{cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2017/03/the-walking-dead-review-something-they-need.html|title=The Walking Dead Review: \"Something They Need\"|first=Josh|last=Jackson|work=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|publisher=[[Wolfgang's Vault]]|date=March 26, 2017|accessdate=April 2, 2017}}</ref><ref name=craveonline>{{cite web|url=http://www.craveonline.com/entertainment/1237575-walking-dead-7-15-something-need-review|title=THE WALKING DEAD 7.15 'Something They Need' Review\n|first=Blair|last=Marnell|work=[[CraveOnline]]|publisher=|date=March 26, 2017|accessdate=April 2, 2017}}</ref><ref name=rollingstone>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/recaps/the-walking-dead-recap-knives-out-w472888|title='The Walking Dead' Recap: Knives Out|first=Noel|last=Murray|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=|date=March 26, 2017|accessdate=April 2, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter filming for the third season of ''The Walking Dead'' ended, Martin-Green was cast in the [[Once Upon a Time (season 2)|second season]] of ''[[Once Upon a Time (TV series)|Once Upon a Time]]'' playing the recurring role of Tamara, a woman determined to rid the world of magic.<ref name=\"Published Wednesday, Jan 2 2013, 18:08 GMT\"/> She returned briefly in the [[Once Upon a Time (season 2)|third season]] before returning to her regular role as Sasha on ''The Walking Dead''. As of the first episode of [[The Walking Dead (season 6)|sixth season]], Martin-Green's name appears in the opening credits.\n\nIn December 2016, her role as the lead actor of ''[[Star Trek: Discovery]]'' as a  lieutenant commander of the USS ''Discovery'' was made public.<ref name=\"EW 2016\">{{cite news|title='Star Trek: Discovery' Casts 'Walking Dead' Actress as Star|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/14/star-trek-discovery-walking-dead-sonequa-martin-green|accessdate=15 December 2016|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=14 December 2016}}</ref> She debuted as First Officer [[Michael Burnham]] in \"[[The Vulcan Hello]]\" on September 24, 2017.\n\n==Personal life==\nMartin-Green has been married to fellow actor Kenric Green since December 4, 2010. They met while acting together in the play, ''[[Fetch Clay, Make Man]]'', at the [[McCarter Theater]] in [[Princeton, New Jersey]]. In 2015, in [[Los Angeles]], Martin-Green gave birth to a boy named Kenric Justin Green, Junior. Martin-Green was pregnant during filming of the [[The Walking Dead (season 5)|fifth season]] of ''The Walking Dead'', which she covered up by wearing thick layers of clothing and using larger guns.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ew.com/article/2015/02/06/walking-dead-star-sonequa-martin-green-explains-how-they-hid-her-pregnancy-show/|title='Walking Dead' star Sonequa Martin-Green explains how they hid her pregnancy on the show|last=Ross|first=Dalton|date=2015-02-06|work=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=2017-09-07|language=en-US}}</ref> She and her husband are vegans.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://americanwaymagazine.com/sonequa-martin-green-set-stun|title=Sonequa Martin-Green is Set to Stun|last=Reilly|first=Phoebe|work=American Way|access-date=2018-04-27}}</ref>\n\nSince April 2016, she has been an ambassador for [[Stand Up to Cancer]], encouraging clinical trials. Her mother is a three-time cancer survivor and her sister has breast cancer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.essence.com/lifestyle/health-wellness/sonequa-martin-cancer-fight|title=Sonequa Martin-Green Is Honoring Her Mother, A Three-Time Cancer Survivor, With This Campaign|last=Robertson|first=Regina A.|date=2018-02-15|work=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=2018-04-27}}</ref>\n\nMartin-Green has been outspoken against situations of injustice and discrimination based on race, gender, and sexual orientation. After the deaths of [[Alton Sterling]] and [[Philando Castile]], she said, \"I push back the hopelessness trying to creep in, believing that God has a plan for all\" before declaring \"Black. Lives. MATTER.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BHksUVkDvaE/|title=Instagram post by Sonequa Martin-Green \u2022 Jul 7, 2016 at 8:15pm UTC|website=Instagram|accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref> After the [[Orlando]] shooting, Martin-Green shared the text message between Mina Justice and her son, Eddie, saying, \"To hear those words from your son... I can't imagine the pain. So many are in so much pain right now. This is tragedy. This is devastation. This is hate. Only love can conquer. Not love that you just speak about, love you put into ACTION. I pray we take action. And I pray that all those touched by this horror will find peace.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sheknows.com/entertainment/articles/1130588/sonequa-martin-green|title=What you should know about Sonequa Martin-Green, the newest Star Trek lead|last=Gemmill|first=Allie|date=2016-12-15|work=SheKnows|access-date=2018-04-27}}</ref> She later joined a charity event supporting the Pulse nightclub victims.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BKcdg3oD4Ee/|title=Sonequa Martin-Green on Instagram: \u201cI believe this event is #loveinaction. And #loveconquersall. #orlandostrong #togetherwecan #togetherwestand\u201d|website=Instagram|accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''Not Quite Right''\n| Coco Delight\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''I-Can-D''\n| VJ\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Blind Thoughts''\n| Jenna Lopez\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2009\n| ''Toe to Toe''\n| Tosha Spinner\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Rivers Wash Over Me]]''\n| Shawna King\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2011\n| ''Da Brick''\n| Rachel\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Yelling to the Sky]]''\n| Jojo Parker\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Shockwave Darkside''\n| Private Lang\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n|''[[Holiday Rush]]''\n|Roxy\n|\n|-\n| 2021\n| ''[[Space Jam 2]]''\n| [[Savannah James]]\n|\n|-\n| {{TBA}}\n| ''[[The Outside Story]]''\n| Isha\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]''\n| Kiana Richmond\n| Episode: \"Legacy\"\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Army Wives]]''\n| Kanessa Jones\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2009\u20132011\n| ''[[The Good Wife]]''\n| Courtney Wells\n| 8 episodes\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Gossip Girl]]''\n| Joanna\n| Episode: \"The Jewel of Denial\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[NYC 22]]''\n| Michelle Terry\n| 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\u20132018\n| ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]''\n| [[Sasha Williams (The Walking Dead)|Sasha Williams]]\n| 45 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Once Upon a Time (TV series)|Once Upon a Time]]''\n| Tamara\n| 7 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Lip Sync Battle]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Sonequa Martin-Green vs. [[Lauren Cohan]]\"\n|-\n| 2016\u20132017\n| ''[[New Girl]]''\n| Rhonda\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Penn Zero: Part-Time Hero]]''\n| Pirate Maria (voice)\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\u2013present\n| ''[[Star Trek: Discovery]]''\n| [[Michael Burnham]] \n| 29 episodes<br>[[Saturn Award for Best Actress on Television]]<br>[[Saturn Award for Best Actress in Streaming Presentation]]\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2020\n| ''[[Star Trek Online]]'' <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arcgames.com/en/games/star-trek-online/news/detail/11357563-star-trek%3A-legacy-now-live%21|title=Star Trek: Legacy Now Live|date=2020-01-28|website=Arcgames|accessdate=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n| Michael Burnham\n| Episode \"Measure of Morality\"\n|-\n| ''Fast & Furious Crossroads''\n| TBA<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SonequaMG/status/1206373204966748160|title=I wish I had a trumpet. Lol! You guys!! I\u2019m so excited to shout out the new video game in the #fastandfurious franchise, FAST & FURIOUS CROSSROADS, coming MAY 2020!!! Your legendary crew is in full effect along with\u2026|last=Martin-Green|first=Sonequa|date=2019-12-15|website=@SonequaMG|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-07}}</ref>\n| \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=2792296|name=Sonequa Martin-Green}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n\n{{Saturn Award for Best Actress on Television}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Martin-Green, Sonequa}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Alabama]]\n[[Category:University of Alabama alumni]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Russellville, Alabama]]\n[[Category:21st-century_Christians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\t\n| name        = Sonequa Martin-Green\t\n| image       = File:Sonequa Martin-Green 2019 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size  = 250px\n| caption     = Martin-Green at the 2019 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\t\n| birth_name  = Sonequa Martin\t\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1985|03|21}}\t\n| birth_place = [[Russellville, Alabama]], U.S.\n| alma_mater  = [[University of Alabama]]\n| occupation  = Actress, producer\n| years_active = 2005\u2013present\t\n| residence   = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S.\t\n| spouse      = {{marriage|[[Kenric Green]]|2010}}\t\n| children = 1\n}}\n\n'''Sonequa Martin-Green''' ({{IPAc-en|s|\u0259|\u02c8|n|i\u02d0|k|w|\u0259}};<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rYr-ttyZ_PQ|title=Sonequa Martin-Green {{!}} Behind the Scenes GH|work=Good Housekeeping|date=October 14, 2015|accessdate=March 28, 2019}}</ref> born March 21, 1985)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/WalkingDead_AMC/status/844247347932663808|title=We're all in for @SonequaMG's birthday. #TWD|last=@WalkingDead_AMC|date=2017-03-21|website=Twitter|accessdate=2017-04-04}}</ref> is an American actress and producer. She is best known for her television roles as [[Michael Burnham]], the main character in the [[web television]] series ''[[Star Trek: Discovery]]'', and as [[Sasha Williams (The Walking Dead)|Sasha Williams]] on ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.highlighthollywood.com/2012/12/31/actress-sonequa-martin-green-does-double-duty-on-abcs-once-upon-a-time-and-amcs-the-walking-dead-highlight-hollywood-news/|title=Actress Sonequa Martin-Green Does Double Duty On ABC's 'Once Upon A Time' And AMC's 'The Walking Dead', Highlight Hollywood News|last=Garrett|first=Tommy Lightfoot|date=2012-12-31|website=Highlight Hollywood|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref> Before that, she had starred in several [[independent films]] before gaining her first recurring role as Courtney Wells on ''[[The Good Wife]]''. Later, she had recurring roles as Tamara in ''[[Once Upon a Time (TV series)|Once Upon a Time]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/12/31/once-upon-time-spoilers-cast-sonequa-martin-green-as-tamara/|title='Once Upon a Time' Season 2 Spoilers \u2014 Sonequa Martin-Green as Tamara|last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|date=2012-12-31|website=TVLine|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/12/31/sonequa-martin-green-once-upon-a-time_n_2389782.html |title='Walking Dead' Actress Sonequa Martin-Green Is Headed To 'Once Upon A Time'|date=2012-12-31|work=HuffPost|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref name=\"Published Wednesday, Jan 2 2013, 18:08 GMT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ustv/s181/once-upon-a-time/news/a438508/walking-dead-actress-sonequa-martin-green-joins-once-upon-a-time.html|title='Walking Dead' actress Sonequa Martin-Green joins 'Once Upon a Time'|last=Fletcher|first=Alex|date=2013-01-02|website=Digital Spy|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.al.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2013/01/ua_theatre_alum_sonequea_marti.html|title=UA theatre alum Sonequa Martin-Green lands role on ABC hit 'Once Upon a Time'|last=Flanagan|first=Ben|date=2013-01-03|website=Al.com|accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref> and Rhonda in ''[[New Girl]]''. \n\n==Early life==\nMartin-Green was born in [[Russellville, Alabama]]. She has one sister and three older half-sisters. She had initially planned to become a [[psychologist]] before deciding to pursue a career in acting when she was in the tenth grade.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wetpaint.com/sonequa-martin-green-5-things-611007/|title=Sonequa Martin-Green: 5 Things You Didn't Know About The Walking Dead Star|last=Lloyd|first=Sarah|date=2013-10-23|work=Wetpaint|access-date=2017-09-07|language=en-US}}</ref> On her decision to become an actor, she said, \"I didn't know I was going to be an actor until I was 16. I thought I was going to be a psychologist, which is interesting because it's very similar to acting. I was fascinated with human behavior and why people do what they do. I was in the middle of rehearsal in 10th grade when I had this epiphany. And so I got my theatre degree from the University of Alabama.\"<ref>{{Cite news|title=Sonequa Martin-Green Shines Bright On Star Trek: Discovery|url=http://www.star2.com/entertainment/2017/09/28/sonequa-martin-green-trek-discovery/|last=Berk|first=Philip|date=2017-09-28|work=star2|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAfter graduating from the [[University of Alabama]] in 2007 with a degree in theatre,<ref name=\"UAalum\">{{cite web|url=http://www.al.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2013/04/ua_alum_sonequa_martin-green_u.html|title=UA alum Sonequa Martin-Green upgraded to 'The Walking Dead' series regular|last=Flanagan|first=Ben|date=April 4, 2013|work=AL.com|accessdate=April 5, 2013}}</ref> she relocated to [[New York City]] where she and her husband, Kenric, lived for five years before moving to [[California]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Film===\nWhile known primarily for her television roles, Sonequa Martin-Green made her film debut in 2009. In 2009, she played the lead role of Tosha Spinner in ''Toe to Toe'' opposite [[Louisa Krause]], the fiercely determined scholarship student who seeks to build a brighter future outside of [[Anacostia]] and away from one of [[Washington, D.C.|Washington]]'s poorest neighborhoods. The film focuses on her friendship and rivalry with Jessie (Louisa Krause), a privileged girl from [[Bethesda, Maryland|Bethesda]] whose promiscuous tendencies threaten to become her undoing. They both strive to gain a better understanding of one another's plight as society threatens to drive them ever farther apart. The film received generally positive reviews, with Martin-Green's performance receiving critical acclaim,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hollywoodandfine.com/%E2%80%98toe-to-toe%E2%80%99-face-to-face-with-race/|title='Toe to Toe': Face to face with race|last=Fine|first=Marchall|date=2010-02-25|website=Hollywood & Fine|language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/04/01/AR2010040100887.html | work=The Washington Post | first=Ann | last=Hornaday | title=Movie review: 'Toe to Toe,' a teen lacrosse drama Washingtonians will recognize | date=2010-04-02}}</ref> even from the film's detractors.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://nypost.com/2010/02/26/schoolgirls-stuck-in-stereotype/ | work=New York Post | first=V.A. | last=Musetto | title=Schoolgirls stuck in stereotype | date=2010-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/toe_to_toe/|title=Toe to Toe|website=Rotten Tomatoes|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref> In November 2018, it was announced Martin-Green would star in ''[[The Outside Story]]'', opposite [[Brian Tyree Henry]], directed by Casimir Nozkowski.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/sonequa-martin-green-brian-tyree-henry-the-outside-story-movie-1202510281/|title=Sonequa Martin-Green Joins Brian Tyree Henry In \u2018The Outside Story\u2019 Movie|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=November 28, 2018|accessdate=November 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Television===\n[[File:Sonequa Martin-Green 2016.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Sonequa Martin-Green at the 2016 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]] for ''The Walking Dead''.]]\nMartin-Green has had various guest and recurring roles in TV shows. She made her television debut in 2008, appearing on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'' as Kiana Richmond. She then gained her first recurring role on ''[[Army Wives]]'' as Kanessa Jones the following year. In 2009, she received the role of Courtney Wells on ''[[The Good Wife]]'', her first recurring role playing an adult character as opposed to playing a teenager with her previous roles in both film and television. She appeared on the show for two years before making two more appearances in ''[[Gossip Girl]]'' and ''[[NYC 22]]'' in 2011.\n\nIn 2012, she was cast in a recurring role on ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]'' as [[Sasha Williams (The Walking Dead)|Sasha]], the sister of Tyreese ([[Chad Coleman]]), an original character, exclusive to the television series.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/walking-dead-season-3-finale-interview-robert-kirkman-431968 |title='Walking Dead' Dissection: Robert Kirkman on the Major Fatalities and Comic Book Detour |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=2013-01-04 |accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref> Martin-Green auditioned for the role of [[Michonne]] albeit with a pseudonym due to the secrecy of the auditioning process. When [[Danai Gurira]], whom Martin-Green said was \"the perfect choice\", was cast, former showrunner [[Glen Mazzara]] still wanted Martin-Green to be a part of the show and decided to create a role specifically for her instead. Martin-Green explained: \"[Sasha] was supposed to be a recurring character and as we kept going forward, they picked up my option to be a regular. It's very rare and I'm still quite dumbfounded about it but Glen and I hit it off and I still appreciate him. He wanted to work with me and wrote Sasha for me.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/gallery/walking-dead-audition-stories-815523/18-sonequa-martingreen-sasha |title='The Walking Dead' Audition Tales: 26 Stars Tell All |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=2015-08-20 |accessdate=2015-08-22}}</ref> She was promoted to a series regular for season 4 with [[Emily Kinney]] and Coleman.<ref>{{cite web|last=Slezak |first=Michael |url=http://tvline.com/2013/04/03/the-walking-dead-season-4-cast-tyreese-sasha-beth-series-regulars/ |title=The Walking Dead's Season 4 Cast \u2014 Tyreese, Sasha, Beth Upgraded To Series Regulars |publisher=TVLine |date= |accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Abrams |first=Natalie |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/entertainment/tv/tvguide/article/The-Walking-Dead-Promotes-Chad-Coleman-Sonequa-4407815.php |title=The Walking Dead Promotes Chad Coleman, Sonequa Martin-Green and More to Series Regular |publisher=seattlepi.com |date= |accessdate=2013-04-04 }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/walking-dead-season-4-spoilers-tyreese-beth-sasha-432869 |title='Walking Dead' Promotes Three to Series Regular for Season 4 |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=2013-03-04 |accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/603070/the-walking-dead-promotes-three-to-series-regulars/ |title='The Walking Dead' Promotes Three To Series Regulars |publisher=Inquisitr.com |date=2009-11-15 |accessdate=2013-04-04}}</ref>\n\nAfter auditioning for the role of Michonne, she read the first three volumes of the graphic novels in preparation for the television series. Knowing they were different, she chose not to continue reading the comic book series to avoid being aware of future storylines that may occur on the television series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3WR6Pt29_Dc|title=Sonequa Martin-Green (AMC's Walking Dead) Interview - AfterBuzz TV's Spotlight On|first=|last=AfterBuzz TV|date=17 February 2014|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> Martin-Green's performance as Sasha, particularly in the [[The Walking Dead (season 5)|fifth season]]<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/the-walking-dead-try-review-ricks-vendetta-against-paul-intensifies-as-finale-looms-10129148.html | location=London | work=The Independent | first=Alex | last=Straker | title=The Walking Dead, Try \u2013 review: Rick Grimes' vendetta against Paul intensifies as finale looms | date=2015-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/tv/the-walking-dead/34129/the-walking-dead-season-5-episode-10-review-them|title=The Walking Dead season 5 episode 10 review: Them|last=Hogan|first=Ron|date=2015-02-16|work=Den of Geek|access-date=2017-09-07|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/tv/the-walking-dead/34461/the-walking-dead-season-5-episode-13-review-forget|title=The Walking Dead season 5 episode 13 review: Forget|last=Hogan|first=Ron|date=2015-03-10|website=Den of Geek|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref> and  [[The Walking Dead (season 7)|seventh season]], has received favorable reviews.<ref name=paste>{{cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2017/03/the-walking-dead-review-something-they-need.html|title=The Walking Dead Review: \"Something They Need\"|first=Josh|last=Jackson|work=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|publisher=[[Wolfgang's Vault]]|date=March 26, 2017|accessdate=April 2, 2017}}</ref><ref name=craveonline>{{cite web|url=http://www.craveonline.com/entertainment/1237575-walking-dead-7-15-something-need-review|title=THE WALKING DEAD 7.15 'Something They Need' Review\n|first=Blair|last=Marnell|work=[[CraveOnline]]|publisher=|date=March 26, 2017|accessdate=April 2, 2017}}</ref><ref name=rollingstone>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/recaps/the-walking-dead-recap-knives-out-w472888|title='The Walking Dead' Recap: Knives Out|first=Noel|last=Murray|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=|date=March 26, 2017|accessdate=April 2, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter filming for the third season of ''The Walking Dead'' ended, Martin-Green was cast in the [[Once Upon a Time (season 2)|second season]] of ''[[Once Upon a Time (TV series)|Once Upon a Time]]'' playing the recurring role of Tamara, a woman determined to rid the world of magic.<ref name=\"Published Wednesday, Jan 2 2013, 18:08 GMT\"/> She returned briefly in the [[Once Upon a Time (season 2)|third season]] before returning to her regular role as Sasha on ''The Walking Dead''. As of the first episode of [[The Walking Dead (season 6)|sixth season]], Martin-Green's name appears in the opening credits.\n\nIn December 2016, her role as the lead actor of ''[[Star Trek: Discovery]]'' as a  lieutenant commander of the USS ''Discovery'' was made public.<ref name=\"EW 2016\">{{cite news|title='Star Trek: Discovery' Casts 'Walking Dead' Actress as Star|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/14/star-trek-discovery-walking-dead-sonequa-martin-green|accessdate=15 December 2016|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=14 December 2016}}</ref> She debuted as First Officer [[Michael Burnham]] in \"[[The Vulcan Hello]]\" on September 24, 2017.\n\n==Personal life==\nMartin-Green has been married to fellow actor Kenric Green since December 4, 2010. They met while acting together in the play, ''[[Fetch Clay, Make Man]]'', at the [[McCarter Theater]] in [[Princeton, New Jersey]]. In 2015, in [[Los Angeles]], Martin-Green gave birth to a boy named Kenric Justin Green, Junior. Martin-Green was pregnant during filming of the [[The Walking Dead (season 5)|fifth season]] of ''The Walking Dead'', which she covered up by wearing thick layers of clothing and using larger guns.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ew.com/article/2015/02/06/walking-dead-star-sonequa-martin-green-explains-how-they-hid-her-pregnancy-show/|title='Walking Dead' star Sonequa Martin-Green explains how they hid her pregnancy on the show|last=Ross|first=Dalton|date=2015-02-06|work=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=2017-09-07|language=en-US}}</ref> She and her husband are vegans.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://americanwaymagazine.com/sonequa-martin-green-set-stun|title=Sonequa Martin-Green is Set to Stun|last=Reilly|first=Phoebe|work=American Way|access-date=2018-04-27}}</ref>\n\nSince April 2016, she has been an ambassador for [[Stand Up to Cancer]], encouraging clinical trials. Her mother is a three-time cancer survivor and her sister has breast cancer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.essence.com/lifestyle/health-wellness/sonequa-martin-cancer-fight|title=Sonequa Martin-Green Is Honoring Her Mother, A Three-Time Cancer Survivor, With This Campaign|last=Robertson|first=Regina A.|date=2018-02-15|work=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=2018-04-27}}</ref>\n\nMartin-Green has been outspoken against situations of injustice and discrimination based on race, gender, and sexual orientation. After the deaths of [[Alton Sterling]] and [[Philando Castile]], she said, \"I push back the hopelessness trying to creep in, believing that God has a plan for all\" before declaring \"Black. Lives. MATTER.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BHksUVkDvaE/|title=Instagram post by Sonequa Martin-Green \u2022 Jul 7, 2016 at 8:15pm UTC|website=Instagram|accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref> After the [[Orlando]] shooting, Martin-Green shared the text message between Mina Justice and her son, Eddie, saying, \"To hear those words from your son... I can't imagine the pain. So many are in so much pain right now. This is tragedy. This is devastation. This is hate. Only love can conquer. Not love that you just speak about, love you put into ACTION. I pray we take action. And I pray that all those touched by this horror will find peace.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sheknows.com/entertainment/articles/1130588/sonequa-martin-green|title=What you should know about Sonequa Martin-Green, the newest Star Trek lead|last=Gemmill|first=Allie|date=2016-12-15|work=SheKnows|access-date=2018-04-27}}</ref> She later joined a charity event supporting the Pulse nightclub victims.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BKcdg3oD4Ee/|title=Sonequa Martin-Green on Instagram: \u201cI believe this event is #loveinaction. And #loveconquersall. #orlandostrong #togetherwecan #togetherwestand\u201d|website=Instagram|accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''Not Quite Right''\n| Coco Delight\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''I-Can-D''\n| VJ\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Blind Thoughts''\n| Jenna Lopez\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2009\n| ''Toe to Toe''\n| Tosha Spinner\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Rivers Wash Over Me]]''\n| Shawna King\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2011\n| ''Da Brick''\n| Rachel\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Yelling to the Sky]]''\n| Jojo Parker\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Shockwave Darkside''\n| Private Lang\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n|''[[Holiday Rush]]''\n|Roxy\n|\n|-\n| 2021\n| ''[[Space Jam 2]]''\n| [[Savannah James]]\n|\n|-\n| {{TBA}}\n| ''[[The Outside Story]]''\n| Isha\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]''\n| Kiana Richmond\n| Episode: \"Legacy\"\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Army Wives]]''\n| Kanessa Jones\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2009\u20132011\n| ''[[The Good Wife]]''\n| Courtney Wells\n| 8 episodes\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Gossip Girl]]''\n| Joanna\n| Episode: \"The Jewel of Denial\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[NYC 22]]''\n| Michelle Terry\n| 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\u20132018\n| ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]''\n| [[Sasha Williams (The Walking Dead)|Sasha Williams]]\n| 45 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Once Upon a Time (TV series)|Once Upon a Time]]''\n| Tamara\n| 7 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Lip Sync Battle]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Sonequa Martin-Green vs. [[Lauren Cohan]]\"\n|-\n| 2016\u20132017\n| ''[[New Girl]]''\n| Rhonda\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Penn Zero: Part-Time Hero]]''\n| Pirate Maria (voice)\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\u2013present\n| ''[[Star Trek: Discovery]]''\n| [[Michael Burnham]] \n| 29 episodes<br>[[Saturn Award for Best Actress on Television]]<br>[[Saturn Award for Best Actress in Streaming Presentation]]\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2020\n| ''[[Star Trek Online]]'' <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arcgames.com/en/games/star-trek-online/news/detail/11357563-star-trek%3A-legacy-now-live%21|title=Star Trek: Legacy Now Live|date=2020-01-28|website=Arcgames|accessdate=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n| Michael Burnham\n| Episode \"Measure of Morality\"\n|-\n| ''Fast & Furious Crossroads''\n| TBA<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SonequaMG/status/1206373204966748160|title=I wish I had a trumpet. Lol! You guys!! I\u2019m so excited to shout out the new video game in the #fastandfurious franchise, FAST & FURIOUS CROSSROADS, coming MAY 2020!!! Your legendary crew is in full effect along with\u2026|last=Martin-Green|first=Sonequa|date=2019-12-15|website=@SonequaMG|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-07}}</ref>\n| \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=2792296|name=Sonequa Martin-Green}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n\n{{Saturn Award for Best Actress on Television}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Martin-Green, Sonequa}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1985 birth