iting history as a designer}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Reynolds |first1=Dan |title=Schriftk\u00fcnstler \u2013 A historiographic examination of the relationship between handcraft and art regarding the design and making of printers\u2019 type in Germany between 1871 and 1914 |date=2020 |publisher=Hochschule f\u00fcr Bildende K\u00fcnste Braunschweig (PhD thesis) |url=https://www.academia.edu/42732982/Chapter_6_Type_design_in_German_foundries_from_1871_to_1914._From_Schriftku_nstler_A_historiographic_examination_of_the_relationship_between_handcraft_and_art_regarding_the_design_and_making_of_printers_type_in_Germany_between_1871_and_1914 |accessdate=21 April 2020 |chapter=Chapter 6: Type design in German foundries from 1871 to 1914}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Schwemer-Scheddin|first=Yvonne|title=Sonderheft G\u00fcnter Gerhard Lange|journal=Typografische Monatsbl\u00e4tter|date=2003}}\n* {{cite book|last=Tracy|first=Walter|author-link=Walter Tracy|title=Letters of Credit: A View of Type Design|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=y8NssjbqNcsC&pg=PA194|date=2003|publisher=D.R. Godine|isbn=978-1-56792-240-0}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n*Berthold pages: [http://www.bertholdtypes.com/font/ag-book/proplus/ AG Book Pro+], [http://www.bertholdtypes.com/font/ag-book-rounded/proplus/ AG Book Rounded], [http://www.bertholdtypes.com/font/ag-book-stencil-et-al/pro/ AG Book Stencil et al], [http://www.bertholdtypes.com/font/ag-old-face/pro/ AG Old Face], [http://www.bertholdtypes.com/font/ag-schoolbook/pro/ AG Schoolbook], [http://www.bertholdtypes.com/font/akzidenz-grotesk/proplus/ Akzidenz-Grotesk Pro+], [http://www.bertholdtypes.com/font/akzidenz-grotesk-next-family/pro/ Akzidenz-Grotesk Next]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110719030422/http://www.sanskritweb.net/fontdocs/#Akzidenz Akzidenz Grotesk sample books] digitised by Ulrich Stiehl\n*[https://www.flickr.com/photos/n1ke/albums/72157629429950223 Berthold specimens from c. 1913], showing Schattierte-Grotesk and co-branding mentioning Berthold and Bauer\n* ''Fonts in Use'' coverage: [https://fontsinuse.com/typefaces/76/akzidenz-grotesk Akzidenz-Grotesk], [https://fontsinuse.com/typefaces/31705/akzidenz-grotesk-condensed AG Condensed], [https://fontsinuse.com/typefaces/7248/ag-book AG Book], [https://fontsinuse.com/typefaces/574/standard Standard] (for American uses)\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/stewf/sets/72157661987768480 Probe 429A] (c. 1960 specimen, photographed by Stephen Coles/Thomas Maier)\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/101656904@N05/sets/72157679746685343 Berthold exklusiv 013: Akzidenz-Grotesk] (1980s Berthold specimen, for phototypesetting)\n* [http://magazines.iaddb.org/issue/GG/1937-08-01/edition/null/page/5 Berthold advertisement from 1937] not showing Akzidenz-Grotesk. The advert showcases \"modern and successful\" faces, illustrating the eclipse of Akzidenz-Grotesk in this period.\n* [http://magazines.iaddb.org/issue/GG/1959-01-01/edition/null/page/68 1959 advert] announcing the arrival of Akzidenz-Grotesk on the Linotype hot metal system\n\n[[Category:Berthold typefaces]]\n[[Category:Grotesque sans-serif typefaces]]\n[[Category:Letterpress typefaces]]\n[[Category:Photocomposition typefaces]]\n[[Category:Typefaces with infant variants]]\n[[Category:Digital typefaces]]\n[[Category:Products introduced in 1898]]\n[[Category:Linotype typefaces]]\n", "name_user": "Blythwood", "label": "safe", "comment": "Converted Tracy's citations to sfn", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akzidenz-Grotesk"}
{"title_page": "Gheorghe Georgescu", "text_new": "{{short description|Romanian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Gheorghe Georgescu\n| image       = \n| image_size  = \n| fullname    = <!-- if different -->\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|1911|07|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Romania]]<ref name=RS>{{RomanianSoccer|776/gheorghe-georgescu.htm}}</ref>\n| death_date  =\n| death_place = \n| height      = \n| position    =  [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]<ref name=RS/>\n| years1 = 1933\u20131934 |clubs1 = Turda Bucure\u0219ti |caps1 =   |goals1 = \n| years2 = 1934\u20131937 |clubs2 = [[FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|Rapid Bucure\u0219ti]]   |caps2 =  40 |goals2 = 8\n| years3 = 1937\u20131938 |clubs3 = [[AS CFR Bra\u0219ov|CFR Bra\u0219ov]]  |caps3 = 15 |goals3 = 4\n| years4 = 1938\u20131940 |clubs4 = [[FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|Rapid Bucure\u0219ti]]      |caps4 = 3 |goals4 = 0\n| totalcaps = 58 | totalgoals =12\n| nationalyears1 = 1935     |nationalteam1 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]]|  nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 1\n}}\n\n'''Gheorghe Georgescu''' (born 15 July 1911; date of death unknown) was a Romanian footballer who played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].<ref>{{WorldFootball|gheorghe-georgescu}}</ref><ref>{{NFT|37328}}</ref> He scored a hat-trick in the 6\u20135 victory against [[FC Ripensia Timi\u0219oara|Ripensia Timi\u0219oara]] in the [[1934\u201335 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]] final, which helped [[FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|Rapid Bucure\u0219ti]] win the first trophy in the club's history.<ref name=finala>{{cite web | url=http://1923.ro/2013/04/finala-cu-un-gol-la-zece-minute/| title=Finala cu un gol la zece minute!| publisher=1923.ro| language=Romanian |trans-title=The final with a goal in every ten minutes! | date=26 April 2013 | accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=RSCUP>{{cite web|url=http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/romanian_cup/1938_1939.shtml|title=Romanian Cup - Season 1938 - 1939|publisher=RomanianSoccer|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nGheorghe Georgescu played three games at international level for [[Romania national football team|Romania]], including two games at the [[1935 Balkan Cup]].<ref name=EU>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=6679|title=Gheorghe Georgescu|publisher=European Football|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref> He scored one goal in a friendly which ended with a 7\u20131 loss against [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]].<ref name=EU/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=14720|title=Bulgaria - Romania 2:0|publisher=European Football|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''Rapid Bucure\u0219ti'''\n*[[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]]: [[1934\u201335 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|1934\u201335]], [[1936\u201337 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|1936\u201337]], [[1938\u201339 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|1938\u201339]]<ref name=finala/><ref name=RSCUP/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.labtof.ro/profil/gheorghe-georgescu-1123/ Gheorghe Georgescu] at Labtof.ro\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Georgescu, Gheorghe}}\n[[Category:1911 births]]\n[[Category:Romanian footballers]]\n[[Category:Romania international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti players]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Romanian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Gheorghe Georgescu\n| image       = \n| image_size  = \n| fullname    = <!-- if different -->\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|1911|07|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Romania]]<ref name=RS>{{RomanianSoccer|776/gheorghe-georgescu.htm}}</ref>\n| death_date  = Unknown\n| death_place = \n| height      = \n| position    =  [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]<ref name=RS/>\n| years1 = 1933\u20131934 |clubs1 = Turda Bucure\u0219ti |caps1 =   |goals1 = \n| years2 = 1934\u20131937 |clubs2 = [[FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|Rapid Bucure\u0219ti]]   |caps2 =  40 |goals2 = 8\n| years3 = 1937\u20131938 |clubs3 = [[AS CFR Bra\u0219ov|CFR Bra\u0219ov]]  |caps3 = 15 |goals3 = 4\n| years4 = 1938\u20131940 |clubs4 = [[FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|Rapid Bucure\u0219ti]]      |caps4 = 3 |goals4 = 0\n| totalcaps = 58 | totalgoals =12\n| nationalyears1 = 1935     |nationalteam1 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]]|  nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 1\n}}\n\n'''Gheorghe Georgescu''' (15 July 1911) was a Romanian footballer who played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].<ref>{{WorldFootball|gheorghe-georgescu}}</ref><ref>{{NFT|37328}}</ref> He scored a hat-trick in the 6\u20135 victory against [[FC Ripensia Timi\u0219oara|Ripensia Timi\u0219oara]] in the [[1934\u201335 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]] final, which helped [[FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|Rapid Bucure\u0219ti]] win the first trophy in the club's history.<ref name=finala>{{cite web | url=http://1923.ro/2013/04/finala-cu-un-gol-la-zece-minute/| title=Finala cu un gol la zece minute!| publisher=1923.ro| language=Romanian |trans-title=The final with a goal in every ten minutes! | date=26 April 2013 | accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=RSCUP>{{cite web|url=http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/romanian_cup/1938_1939.shtml|title=Romanian Cup - Season 1938 - 1939|publisher=RomanianSoccer|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nGheorghe Georgescu played three games at international level for [[Romania national football team|Romania]], including two games at the [[1935 Balkan Cup]].<ref name=EU>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=6679|title=Gheorghe Georgescu|publisher=European Football|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref> He scored one goal in a friendly which ended with a 7\u20131 loss against [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]].<ref name=EU/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=14720|title=Bulgaria - Romania 2:0|publisher=European Football|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''Rapid Bucure\u0219ti'''\n*[[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]]: [[1934\u201335 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|1934\u201335]], [[1936\u201337 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|1936\u201337]], [[1938\u201339 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|1938\u201339]]<ref name=finala/><ref name=RSCUP/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.labtof.ro/profil/gheorghe-georgescu-1123/ Gheorghe Georgescu] at Labtof.ro\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Georgescu, Gheorghe}}\n[[Category:1911 births]]\n[[Category:Romanian footballers]]\n[[Category:Romania international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti players]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n", "name_user": "S.A. Julio", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gheorghe_Georgescu"}
{"title_page": "Srushti Dange", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Srushti Dange\n| image              = Srushti Dange.jpg\n| caption            = Srushti Dange at ''[[Saravanan Irukka Bayamaen]]'' press meet\n| birth_name         = Srushthi Danghe\n| birth_date         = <!--Birthdate must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs. No IMDb. No public records. See WP:BLPPRIVACY-->\n| birth_place        = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| nationality        = India\n| othername          = Actress\n| occupation         = \n| yearsactive        = 2013\u2013present\n| spouse             = \n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Srushti Dange''' is an Indian actress, who has mostly appeared in Tamil films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tamilmoviemistakes.blogspot.com/2014/10/megha-2014-film-movie-mistakes.html|title=Tamil Movie Mistakes: 175. Megha (2014 film) Movie Mistakes|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/shotcuts-the-south-connect/article4711425.ece|title =Shot cuts the south connect|work =[[The Hindu]]|author=Nikhil Raghavan|date=13 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kollywoodtoday.net/news/tollywood-girl-debuts-in-varusanaadu|title=Tollywood girl's kollywood debut|work=Kollywood today|date=8 June 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nSrushti Dange initially appeared in supporting roles, playing a victim in [[Myshkin (director)|Myshkin]]'s ''[[Yuddham Sei]]'' (2011), before playing a supporting role in the Telugu film, ''[[April Fool (2014 film)|April Fool]]''.<ref>[http://www.telugumirchi.com/en/movies/srushti-dangean-a-grade-scribe.html \"Srushti Dange, an A grade scribe\"]. telugumirchi.com. 11 April 2012</ref> Srusthi made a breakthrough portraying the lead role in the romantic thriller ''[[Megha (2014 film)|Megha]]'', winning mixed reviews for her performance in the title role. 2015 she was seen in the horror film ''[[Darling (2015 Tamil film)|Darling]]'' and the psychological thriller film ''[[Enakkul Oruvan (2015 film)|Enakkul Oruvan]]''.\n\nSrushti has completed work on ''[[Puriyadha Anandam Puthithaga Arambam|Puriyatha Anandam Puthithaga Arambam]]'', a romantic film which launches [[Krish (singer)|Krish]] in the leading role. She is currently working on four Tamil films: the ''[[Dharma Durai (2016 film)|Dharma Durai]]'',<ref>[http://silverscreen.in/news/srushti-dange-on-a-roll/ \"Srushti Dange on a Roll\"]. ''Silverscreen.in''. 1 September 2014</ref> [[Vijay Vasanth]]'s ''[[Achamindri]]'', the romantic comedy ''[[Navarasa Thilagam]]'', in which she plays a medical student, and the [[Suseenthiran]] production ''[[Vil Ambu]]''.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/Packing-Punches-in-Acchamindri/2015/04/06article2749237.ece</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Language !! Notes\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Kadhalagi]]'' || Nandhini Velu Nachiyar || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Yuddham Sei]]'' || Suja || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[April Fool (2014 film)|April Fool]]'' || Satya || Telugu ||\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Megha (2014 film)|Megha]]'' || Meghavathy || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Darling (2015 Tamil film)|Darling]]'' || Swati || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Oru Nodiyil'' || Savi  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Enakkul Oruvan (2015 film)|Enakkul Oruvan]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Puriyadha Anandam Puthithaga Arambam]]'' || Nila || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Kaththukkutti]]'' || Bhuvana || Tamil || [[Edison Awards (India)|Edison Award for Best Actress in a Social Awareness Movie]] \n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Vil Ambu]]'' || Nithya || Tamil ||\n|-\