{"title_page": "1987 U.S. Figure Skating Championships", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=March 2014}}\n{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition\n| title = 1987 United States Figure Skating Championships\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| comptype = National Championship\n| startdate = January\n| enddate = \n| skatingseason = 1986\u201387\n| location = [[Tacoma, Washington]]\n| host = \n| venue = \n| prizemoney = \n| defendladies = \n| defenddance = \n| championmen = [[Brian Boitano]]\n| championladies = [[Jill Trenary]]\n| championpairs = [[Jill Watson]] / [[Peter Oppegard]]\n| championdance = [[Suzanne Semanick]] / [[Scott Gregory (ice skater)|Scott Gregory]]\n| previouscomp = [[1986 United States Figure Skating Championships|1986 U.S. Championships]]\n| nextcomp = [[1988 United States Figure Skating Championships|1988 U.S. Championships]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1987 [[United States Figure Skating Championships]]''' was an event organized by [[U.S. Figure Skating]] to determine the U.S. national champions in [[figure skating]]. The event was one of the criteria used to select the U.S. teams for the [[1987 World Figure Skating Championships|1987 World Championships]]. Medals were awarded in four colors: gold (first), silver (second), bronze (third), and pewter (fourth) in four disciplines \u2013 [[single skating|men's singles, ladies' singles]], [[pair skating]], and [[ice dancing]] \u2013 across three levels: senior, junior, and novice. The 1987 Championships took place in January 1987 at the [[Tacoma Dome]] in [[Tacoma, Washington]].<ref name=NT150530/><ref name=WP870208/>\n\n==Senior-level results==\n===Men===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Name\n! CF\n! SP\n! FS\n|- bgcolor=\"gold\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''1'''\n| [[Brian Boitano]] ||1||1||\n|- bgcolor=\"silver\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''2'''\n| [[Christopher Bowman]] ||||2||\n|- bgcolor=\"cc9966\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''3'''\n| [[Scott Williams (figure skater)|Scott Williams]] ||3||||\n|- bgco